		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014 SI"></a><br><code>sle2014s/paper05</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Practical domain-specific debuggers using the Moldable Debugger framework</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AndreiChiș.html">Andrei Chiș</a>, <a href="../profile/MarcusDenker.html">Marcus Denker</a>, <a href="../profile/TudorGîrba.html">Tudor Gîrba</a>, <a href="../profile/OscarNierstrasz.html">Oscar Nierstrasz</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.cl.2015.08.005">10.1016/j.cl.2015.08.005</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2014/paper06.html"><em>The Moldable Debugger: A Framework for Developing Domain-Specific Debuggers</em></a> (SLE 2014)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The central contribution is a framework (tooling/workbench support) for constructing domain-specific debuggers via reusable operations and views.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> The work is about inspecting and interacting with running program executions (debugging runtime behavior).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> A primary motivation is improving developer workflow and reducing the abstraction gap/cognitive load through tailored debugging views.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> The paper discusses implementation strategies and their performance impact (notably overhead being opt-in).
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
